 Ofcom 表示，TikTok 是 12-15 岁青少年最受欢迎的新闻来源https://www.nme.com/news/tiktok-is-the-most-popular-news-source-for-12-15-year-olds-says-ofcom-3472186?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=tiktok-is-the-most-popular-news-source-for-12-15-year-olds-says-ofcomWill Richards Sun, 23 Jul 2023 21:51:53 +0000 NewsTikTok https://www.nme.com/?p=3472186 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="抖音" decoding="async" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>它已取代 YouTube 和 Instagram 成为该年龄段的主要新闻来源</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tiktok-is-the-most-popular-news-source-for-12-15-year-olds-says-ofcom-3472186">Ofcom 表示，TikTok 是 12-15 岁青少年最受欢迎的新闻来源，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="抖音" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tiktok-logo-app-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Ofcom 的新研究显示， <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/tiktok">TikTok</a>目前是 12 至 15 岁青少年最受欢迎的新闻来源。</p><p>该通信监管机构的最新报告显示，该视频应用程序已超越 Instagram 和 YouTube，成为该年龄段的主要新闻提供商。</p><p> TikTok 目前向 28% 的 12 岁至 15 岁儿童提供新闻，YouTube 和 Instagram 的比例均为 25%。</p><p>尽管如此，BBC 通过其所有频道（从电视到社交媒体、广播等）覆盖了该年龄段 39% 的受众。</p><p>现在，每 10 个成年人中就有一个使用 TikTok 作为新闻来源，超过了第 5 频道和 BBC 广播 1 台。</p><p> 16 至 24 岁的人从社交媒体获取新闻的可能性也比成年人高出 30%，该年龄段中只有 6% 的人会在线访问传统新闻网站。 </p><figure id="attachment_3414706" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3414706" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3414706" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/tik-tok-banned-government-phones-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3414706" class="wp-caption-text"> TikTok 徽标（图片来源：Michele Ursi / Alamy Stock Photo）。</figcaption></figure><p>早在三月份，由于这款中国应用程序的安全问题<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tiktok-banned-from-uk-government-phones-3414685">，英国政府就禁止使用 TikTok</a> 。</p><p>英国内阁办公室部长奥利弗·道登在向议会发表的一份声明中表示，这款由中国公司字节跳动拥有的视频共享应用程序将立即被禁止。</p><p>此举使英国与美国和欧盟委员会保持一致，此前<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/uk-security-minister-requests-ncsc-investigation-into-tiktok-3413247">英国安全部长汤姆·图根哈特 (Tom Tugendhat) 本周早些时候要求 NCSC 针对潜在的安全风险对</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/tiktok">TikTok</a>进行调查。</p><p>他告诉<a href="https://news.sky.com/story/tiktok-ban-minister-asks-national-cyber-security-centre-to-look-into-safety-of-app-12833371" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>天空新闻</em></a>，保持英国“外交进程的自由和安全”“绝对必要”。</p><p>同月，美国众议院外交事务委员会<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/tiktok-could-be-banned-in-the-us-after-bill-advances-3406647">以24比16投票，赋予总统乔·拜登在全国范围内实施对TikTok的禁令的权力</a>。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tiktok-is-the-most-popular-news-source-for-12-15-year-olds-says-ofcom-3472186">Ofcom 表示，TikTok 是 12-15 岁青少年最受欢迎的新闻来源，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
